  "instructions": [
    "Toast the sesame seeds in a dry skillet over medium heat for about 3 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "In a pan, sauté minced garlic and onion with ground cumin until fragrant and slightly translucent.",
    "Add the toasted sesame seeds to the pan, then mix well with the garlic-onion-cumin mixture.",
    "Gradually drizzle in the sesame seed oil while continuously stirring to prevent burning. Continue cooking for about 2 minutes.",
    "Season with a pinch of salt to taste. If desired, stir in chopped cilantro leaves.",
    "Serve immediately as a snack or side dish."
